# Graphify — Solo-Dev & Low-End Hardware

StudyForge **deviates** from official Graphify team recommendations. This is intentional: **solo developer**, **low-end local machine**, **remote gets one current snapshot only**.

## Remote Git Policy (contrary to upstream team docs)

| Commit to GitHub | Never commit |
|------------------|--------------|
| `graphify-out/graph.json` | `graphify-out/cache/` |
| `graphify-out/GRAPH_REPORT.md` | `graphify-out/memory/` |
| | `graphify-out/wiki/` |
| | `graphify-out/graph.html` |
| | Graph version history / incremental memory |

**Replace, don't accumulate:** Each push should reflect the **latest** `graphify update` only. No historical graph snapshots in the repo.

## Low-End Dev Modus Operandi

- **Use:** `npm run graphify:refresh` (AST-only, no LLM cost)
- **Avoid:** `graphify watch` (continuous CPU/disk)
- **Avoid:** `graphify hook install` (auto rebuild every commit)
- **Avoid:** `graphify save-result` / `graphify-out/memory/` (feedback-loop history)
- **Prefer:** Read `graphify-out/GRAPH_REPORT.md` before opening many source files
- **CLI queries:** `graphify query "<question>" --budget 1500` to cap tokens on weak hardware
- **MCP:** Default `.mcp.example.json` = graphify only. Enable `code-review-graph` via `.mcp.example.full.json` only on capable machines (embeddings are heavy).

## When to Refresh

Run refresh **before** `git push` when `src/`, `lib/`, or `workers/` changed materially:

```bash
npm run graphify:refresh
git add graphify-out/graph.json graphify-out/GRAPH_REPORT.md
```

Agents may run refresh after large refactors in-session; do not run in parallel with `npm run dev` on low-end RAM.

## Agent Navigation Order

1. `graphify-out/GRAPH_REPORT.md` (god nodes, communities)
2. `graphify query` or MCP `graphify-studyforge` (budget-capped)
3. Targeted `@src/...` file reads
4. Broad `grep` only as last resort

<example>
npm run graphify:refresh && git add graphify-out/graph.json graphify-out/GRAPH_REPORT.md
</example>

<example type="invalid">
git add graphify-out/cache/ graphify-out/memory/   # bloats remote, breaks solo policy
graphify watch .   # continuous rebuild on low-end laptop
</example>

## Ignore Extraction Bloat

`@.graphifyignore` excludes `node_modules/`, `dist/`, locks, and local cache paths for faster updates.
